Snowball
 - Petabyte-scale data transport solution that uses secures appliances to transfer large amounts of data into and out of AWS.
 - Using Snowball addresses common challenges whith large-scale data transfers including high network cost, long transfer time, 
 and security concerns.
 - Transfer data is simple, fast, secure, and can be as little as one-fifth the cost of high-speed internet.
 - 80TB in all regions
 - Multiple layers of security:
  - Tamper-resistant enclosures
  - 256-bit encryption
  - Industry-standard Trusted Plataform Module (TPM)
  - Once the data transfer job has processed and verified

Snowball-Edge
  - 100TB data transfer device with on-board storage and compute capabilities.
  - Use to move large amounts of data into and out of AWS, as a temporary storage tier for large local datasets or to support
  local workloads in remote or offline locations
  - Connect to your existing applications and infrastructure using standard storage interfaces, streamilining the data transfer
  process and minimizing setup integration.
  - Can Cluster together to form a local storage tier and process your data on premisses, helping ensure your applications
  to continue run even when they are not able to acces the cloud

Snowmobile
  - Exabyte data transfer service used to move extremely large amounts of data to AWS
  - Can transfer 100PB per Snowmobile, a 45-foot long ruggedized shipping container, pulled by semi-trailer truck
  - Make easy to move volumes of data, including video libraries, image repositories, or even a complete data center migration
  - Secure, fast and cost effective

Exams Tips:
  - Understand what Snowball is
  - Understand what import export is
  - Snowball can
    - import to S3
    - export from S3
    